A shooting at Westroads Mall in Omaha left several injured and eight dead, including the gunman, Robert A. Hawkins.
The incident was described as random and without provocation.
Hawkins, who had a troubled life, left a note expressing remorse before taking his own life.
President George W. Bush had left the area just before the shooting occurred.
The victims included employees and customers, with some in critical condition.
The mall remained closed as authorities investigated the motive behind the tragic event.
Grief counseling was offered to those affected by the senseless violence.
